<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>ðŸ‘‹ HelloTrello</title>
  <!-- capture the CSS content as a Nunjucks variable -->
  {% set css %}
    {% include "style.css" %}
  {% endset %}
  <!-- feed it through our cssmin filter to minify -->
  <style>
    {{ css | cssmin | safe }}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="tint">
    <header>
      <h1>HelloTrello!</h1>
      <p>
        This site is populated with content from a public <a href="https://trello.com/b/Zzc0USwZ/hellotrello">Trello board</a>. Every deployment pulls the  content from the Trello API and generates the site's HTML at build time on <a href="https://netlify.com">Netlify</a>.
      </p>
    </header>
  </div>
  <main>
    {% for card in trello %}
    <section>
      <h2>{{ card.name }} </h2>
      <div>
      {% markdown %}
        {{- card.desc }}
      {% endmarkdown %}
      </div>
    </section>
    {% endfor %}
  </main>
  <div class="tint">
    <footer>
      <p>
        This example includes <a href="https://stage--hellotrello.netlify.app">staging</a> and <a href="https://hellotrello.netlify.app">production</a> environments. Go ahead, take a look.
      </p>
      <p>
        Environments are created by <a href="https://docs.netlify.com/site-deploys/overview/#branches-and-deploys">Netlify's Branch Deploy</a> feature, but the code on each branch is identical â€” they simply filter the content included based on the labels on the Trello cards and the branch name.
      </p>
      <p>
        Feel free to explore this site's <a href="{{ pkg.repository.url }}">code in GitHub</a> to learn more and try this out for yourself.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
